<emphasis id="B91BEABCC642FF84FF14FB8FCF26FB2A" bold="true" box="[151,777,1130,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="4C6F4D2DC642FF84FF14FB8FCD8AFB2A" box="[151,421,1130,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Erythria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuspiprojecta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B91BEABCC642FF84FF14FB8FCD8AFB2A" bold="true" box="[151,421,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Erythria cuspiprojecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22857C7C642FF84FE2EFB8FCE25FB2A" box="[429,522,1130,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FD99FB8FCE86FB2A" box="[538,681,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,192,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[214,1373,155,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3, dorsal view; 4 – 6, lateral view; 7 – 9, face; 1, 4, 7, Erythria calvusa sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8, E. cuspiprojecta sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9, E. euryprojecta sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FDDDFB8FCEA4FB2A" box="[606,651,1130,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="2.5">2, 5</number>
, 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FD1AFB8FCE86FB2A" box="[665,681,1130,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="15.08" valueMax="22.0" valueMin="8.16">8</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FD35FB8FCF2FFB2A" box="[694,768,1130,1156]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,206,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Erythria cuspiprojecta sp. nov. 16, Crown, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; 17, pygofer side, lateral view; 18, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; aedeagus, lateral view; 19, paramere, lateral view; 20, connective, dorsal view; 21, aedeagus, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">16–22</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036AEC642FF84FF14FB54CDB3FA9B" blockId="1.[151,1436,1201,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Body brown. Pair of round brownish-black patches at sides of coronal suture and other irregularly shaped dark brown patches on pronotum, scutum orange-yellow with three blackish patches, scutellum yellowish brown (
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FAECFB30CC87FABF" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[239,1341,192,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[214,1373,155,1953]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. 1 – 3, dorsal view; 4 – 6, lateral view; 7 – 9, face; 1, 4, 7, Erythria calvusa sp. nov.; 2, 5, 8, E. cuspiprojecta sp. nov.; 3, 6, 9, E. euryprojecta sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281276/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FF14FB1CCC87FABF" box="[151,168,1273,1297]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Fore wing yellowish brown with patches between light bordered veins, hind wing weakly semitransparent with veins yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3756525C642FF84FF4AFAA4C860FA47" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD036AEC642FF84FF4AFAA4CDA4FA6B" blockId="1.[151,1436,1201,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B91BEABCC642FF84FF4AFAA4CD42FAF7" box="[201,365,1345,1369]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer with sclerotized appendage at its blunt hind upper angle (
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FBDFFAA4C880FAF7" box="[1116,1199,1345,1369]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,206,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Erythria cuspiprojecta sp. nov. 16, Crown, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; 17, pygofer side, lateral view; 18, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; aedeagus, lateral view; 19, paramere, lateral view; 20, connective, dorsal view; 21, aedeagus, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FB13FAA4C880FAF7" box="[1168,1199,1345,1369]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
). Margin of subgenital plate folded dorsad at midlength with apex rounded (
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FC9CFA80CF5BFAD3" box="[799,884,1381,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,206,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Erythria cuspiprojecta sp. nov. 16, Crown, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; 17, pygofer side, lateral view; 18, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; aedeagus, lateral view; 19, paramere, lateral view; 20, connective, dorsal view; 21, aedeagus, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FCD6FA80CF5BFAD3" box="[853,884,1381,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apical extension of paramere straight, tapered (
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FF1CFA6CCCDCFA0F" box="[159,243,1417,1441]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,206,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Erythria cuspiprojecta sp. nov. 16, Crown, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; 17, pygofer side, lateral view; 18, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; aedeagus, lateral view; 19, paramere, lateral view; 20, connective, dorsal view; 21, aedeagus, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Fig. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FF57FA6CCCDCFA0F" box="[212,243,1417,1441]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Penis stem smooth, with narrow apodeme and two long, thin apical processes pointed apically (
<figureCitation id="13542A2BC642FF84FABAFA6CCC98FA6B" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 22" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1578,1601]" captionTargetBox="[173,1409,206,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1557]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 22. Erythria cuspiprojecta sp. nov. 16, Crown, pronotum and scutellum, dorsal view; 17, pygofer side, lateral view; 18, subgenital plate, paramere, connective and valve, dorsal view; aedeagus, lateral view; 19, paramere, lateral view; 20, connective, dorsal view; 21, aedeagus, lateral view; 22, aedeagus, hind view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281278/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number id="3DA72489C642FF84FAFAFA6CCC98FA6B" pageId="1" pageNumber="61" value="21.22">21, 22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD036AEC642FF84FF4AFA37C860FA47" blockId="1.[151,1436,1201,1765]" box="[201,1103,1489,1513]" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B91BEABCC642FF84FF4AFA37CD4FFA47" box="[201,352,1490,1513]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="61">Measurement</emphasis>
: Male 2.9 mm (including wing); Female 3.0 mm (including wing).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
